Contract CO1: createTask
Operation:
createTask(String title, String description, PriorityLevel priorityLevel,
           LocalDate dueDate, RecurrencePattern recurrence)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A task title is provided (either valid or invalid).
  - A priority level is provided.

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - The task title is valid (not empty).
  - No existing task has the same title and due date combination.
  - If dueDate is null, the count of open undated tasks is below 50 (OCL maxUndatedOpenTasks).
  - A new Task object is created.
  - The Task attributes (taskId, title, description, priorityLevel, dueDate, creation date, status=OPEN) are set.
  - If recurrence is provided, TaskOccurrence objects are generated and associated with the Task.
  - The Task is stored in the TaskRepository.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task.
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes (timestamp and description) are set to indicate that the task was created.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario):
  - The task title is missing/invalid, OR a task with the same title and due date already exists,
    OR the 50 undated open tasks OCL constraint is violated.
  - There is no Task object created.
  - There is no system data modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The state of the system remains unchanged.


Contract CO2: updateTask
Operation:
updateTask(String taskId, String title, String description,
           PriorityLevel priorityLevel, LocalDate dueDate,
           RecurrencePattern recurrence)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A task identifier (taskId) is provided.

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - One or more Task attributes (title, description, priorityLevel, dueDate, recurrence) are updated.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task.
  - The ActivityEntry attributes (timestamp and description) are set.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario):
  - There is no Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no task attributes modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.


