  - There is no system data modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The state of the system remains unchanged.


Contract CO7: assignTaskToProject
Operation:
assignTaskToProject(String taskId, String projectId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A task identifier (taskId) is provided.
  - A project identifier (projectId) is provided.

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is a Project object with the given projectId in the system.
  - The association between the Task and the Project is created.
  - The Project's task list is updated to include the Task.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task.
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes (timestamp and description) are set to indicate that the task was assigned to a project.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when task not found):
  - There is no Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no association created.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The state of the system remains unchanged.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when project not found):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no Project object with the given projectId in the system.
  - There is no association created.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The state of the system remains unchanged.


Contract CO8: removeTaskFromProject
Operation:
removeTaskFromProject(String taskId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A task identifier (taskId) is provided.

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - The association between the Task and its Project is removed.
  - The Task no longer belongs to any Project.
  - The Project's task list no longer includes the Task.
  - The Task object itself remains in the system.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task.
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes (timestamp and description) are set to indicate that the task was removed from its project.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario):
  - There is no Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no task-project association modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.


Contract CO9: moveTaskToProject
Operation:
moveTaskToProject(String taskId, String newProjectId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A task identifier (taskId) is provided.
  - A project identifier (newProjectId) is provided.

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is a Project object with the given newProjectId in the system.
  - The association between the Task and its previous Project is removed.
  - The association between the Task and the new Project is created.
  - The previous Project's task list no longer includes the Task.
  - The new Project's task list includes the Task.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the Task.
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes (timestamp and description) are set to indicate that the task was moved to another project.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when task is not found):
  - There is no Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no task-project association modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when project is not found):
  - There is a Task object with the given taskId in the system.
  - There is no Project object with the given newProjectId in the system.
  - There is no task-project association modified.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.


Contract CO10: createSubtask
Operation:
createSubtask(String parentTaskId, String title)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - A parent task identifier (parentTaskId) is provided.
  - A subtask title is provided (either valid or invalid).

Postcondition (Success Scenario):
  - There is a Task object with the given parentTaskId in the system.
  - The subtask title is valid (not empty).
  - The parent Task's subtasks count is below 20 (OCL maxSubtasks).
  - A new Subtask object is created.
  - The Subtask's attributes (subtaskId, title, status, creation date) are set.
  - The Subtask is associated with the parent Task.
  - The parent Task's subtask list includes the new Subtask.
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created.
  - The ActivityEntry is associated with the parent Task.
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes (timestamp and description) are set to indicate that a subtask was created.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when parent task is not found):
  - There is no Task object with the given parentTaskId in the system.
  - There is no Subtask object created.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.

Postcondition (Failure Scenario when the subtask's title is invalid or OCL is violated):
  - There is a Task object with the given parentTaskId in the system.
  - The subtask title is missing/invalid, OR the subtask limit of 20 is reached.
  - There is no Subtask object created.
  - There is no ActivityEntry object created.
  - The system state remains unchanged.


